# Port Coverage Set (Vertex Cover)

## Context
Coverage set finds a minimal set of nodes that "covers" all edges - useful for understanding which issues touch the most dependency relationships.

## Go Implementation Reference
```go
// generateCoverageSet in advanced_insights.go
// Greedy 2-approximation vertex cover
```

## Rust Implementation (advanced/coverage.rs)
```rust
use crate::graph::DiGraph;

pub struct CoverageItem {
    pub node: usize,
    pub edges_added: usize,
}

pub struct CoverageResult {
    pub items: Vec<CoverageItem>,
    pub edges_covered: usize,
    pub total_edges: usize,
}

/// Greedy vertex cover - 2-approximation algorithm.
pub fn coverage_set(graph: &DiGraph, limit: usize) -> CoverageResult {
    let n = graph.node_count();
    let total_edges = graph.edge_count();

    // Track covered edges
    let mut covered = vec![vec![false; n]; n];
    let mut edges_covered = 0;
    let mut selected = Vec::new();

    for _ in 0..limit {
        // Find node covering most uncovered edges
        let mut best_node = None;
        let mut best_count = 0;

        for v in 0..n {
            let mut count = 0;
            // Count uncovered outgoing edges
            for &w in graph.successors(v) {
                if !covered[v][w] { count += 1; }
            }
            // Count uncovered incoming edges
            for &u in graph.predecessors(v) {
                if !covered[u][v] { count += 1; }
            }

            if count > best_count {
                best_count = count;
                best_node = Some(v);
            }
        }

        match best_node {
            Some(node) if best_count > 0 => {
                // Mark edges as covered
                for &w in graph.successors(node) {
                    covered[node][w] = true;
                }
                for &u in graph.predecessors(node) {
                    covered[u][node] = true;
                }

                selected.push(CoverageItem {
                    node,
                    edges_added: best_count,
                });
                edges_covered += best_count;
            }
            _ => break,
        }
    }

    CoverageResult {
        items: selected,
        edges_covered,
        total_edges,
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Greedy covers edges efficiently
- [ ] Returns coverage ratio
- [ ] Respects limit parameter

notes:
CRITICAL FIX: Replace O(nÂ²) memory vec![vec![false; n]; n] with HashSet<(usize, usize)>. For 1000-node graph, matrix = 1MB vs HashSet = O(E) bytes. Updated implementation:

